Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Slice @precooked polenta{8.8%ounce} into 8-10 ½-inch-thick rounds (you'll have 16-20 rounds for 4). Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.

== Roasted Green Beans & Polenta Cakes ==

Toss green beans on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} (for 4 servings, spread out across entire sheet).

Lightly oil empty side of baking sheet. Place polenta slices on oiled side of sheet (for 4, place polenta on a second lightly oiled baking sheet). Season with a pinch of salt and pepper; sprinkle tops with @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}.

Roast on top rack until green beans are tender and polenta cakes are lightly browned, ~{12-15%minutes}. (For 4, roast green beans on top rack and polenta cakes on middle rack.)

== Steak ==

Meanwhile, pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season generously all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

== Mushroom Sauce ==

Heat @butter{1%tablespoon} and a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for steak over medium heat. Add mushrooms and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are slightly crispy, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/3%cup}, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan. Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat and whisk in @crème fraîche{2%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Divide steak, polenta cakes, and green beans between plates in separate sections. Spoon mushroom sauce over steak and serve.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.